<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/eu-leaders-rebuff-calls-action-europes-migration-crisis-145541266.html"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/Njon72zYaf_H9dBMHJCfow--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9NzU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2013-10-25T145541Z_1_CBRE99O15H000_RTROPTP_2_EU-SUMMIT.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="Lithuania&#039;s President Grybauskaite arrives at a European Union leaders summit in Brussels" align="left" title="Lithuania&#039;s President Grybauskaite arrives at a European Union leaders summit in Brussels" border="0" /></a>By Adrian Croft and Justyna Pawlak BRUSSELS (Reuters) - European Union leaders rebuffed calls from southern European states on Friday for emergency action to tackle a wave of illegal migration from Africa despite the deaths of hundreds of people in Mediterranean boat disasters. EU leaders meeting in Brussels expressed &quot;deep sadness&quot; at the drownings, which have killed up to 550 migrants this month alone, but postponed any new action until December. </p><br clear="all"/>
